BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Jpr-lFxiDdjFpn9p-DYAA
SUMMARY:Get Grant Ready - VIRTUAL
DTSTAMP:20260307T213102Z
DTSTART:20260311T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description    Get Grant Ready: Grants Preparedness Workshop fo
	r Micro Businesses Virtual - March 10 - 2pm Join GSBA for a practical Spri
	ng workshop focused on helping small and micro businesses break down barri
	ers to securing grants. About This Workshop Facilitated by GSBA's Grant Wr
	iter & Manager\, Devonshire Lokke\, this Spring workshop will focus on bre
	aking down barriers to securing grants for small and micro business. Topic
	s will include grant research \\(where to find grants for small businesses
	\\)\, grant writing \\(how to apply for grants\\)\, budgeting \\(how to tr
	ack and manage grant funds\\)\, and reporting \\(how to share successes an
	d challenges with funders\\). As a grant writer and manager for 6\\+ years
	\, Devonshire knows that grants can seem intimidating and overwhelming\, e
	specially for a small or micro-business owner. This workshop will provide 
	entrepreneurs with the confidence\, tools\, and resources to quickly and c
	ompetitively pursue future grant opportunities \\(presented by both GSBA a
	nd other funders\\). Workshops will be open to GSBA members and non-member
	s and will be in person at the GSBA offices in Capitol Hill\, Seattle. The
	 session will conclude with 30 minutes of Q&A\, to address participants' u
	nique business needs. What You'll Learn Where to find grant opportunities 
	relevant to small and micro businesses How to read and assess grant requir
	ements before applying Best practices for grant applications and narrative
	s How to build and track grant budgets with confidence What funders expect
	 in grant reporting and follow-up Common pitfalls-and how to avoid them Wh
	o Should Attend Micro businesses and sole proprietors Early-stage entrepre
	neurs Businesses applying for grants for the first time Businesses that ha
	ve applied before but want stronger results Business owners seeking clear\
	, practical guidance No prior grant experience is required.\n\nhttps://sea
	today.6amcity.com/events/#/details/get-grant-ready-virtual/18234874/2026-0
	3-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/get-grant-ready-virtual/1
	8234874/2026-03-11T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
